Confluence is nearly unusable on small screens like a mobile phone or Pocket PC. It would be useful to have a theme that auto-activates when on a non-PC client, which eliminates or simplifies the surrounding screen elements that a mobile user probably won't need. I doubt many people want to edit a Confluence page from a mobile device (though this would be good to have) but viewing them would be great. I get frequent email notifications of changes to Confluence page changes from remote and it would be very useful to be able to review the changes from a mobile device.

